 >> I have what may be a real "novice" question. When PGP is finally
 >> "cracked/broken" will it then be a relatively simple matter to decode
 >> data encrypted with it ? Or will it be neccessary to mount the same
 >> massive initial effort for each attempt at decrypting a message ? I hope
 >> someone can help me with this as i am a real newcomer to this forum.

That depends on how you define "simple", and fow whom?  Unless somebody
discovers a glaring security breach in the IDEA or RSA encryption
algorithms, then there will probably be no "simple" way for people with
average computers to break PGP.

